INFO

- this is an altered version of direwolf https://github.com/wb2osz/direwolf/tree/master/src

DIREWOLF CHANGES

- redefined packet length in hdlc_rec2, hdlc_rec, rrdb
- adding custom decoding in duty_cyclists_decoder
- bypassed crc check (error detection) and multi_modem_process_rec_frame (sends frame for ax25) from try_decode2() in hdlc_rec2
- added libfec to external 

TODO

- write to json
- see known issues

Duty Cyclists packet standard:
_________________________________________________________________________
|               |               |               |                       |
|   Byte 0      |   Bytes 1-5   |   Bytes 6-10  |   Bytes 11-17         |
|   Radio ID    |   Latitude    |   Longitude   |   Error Correction    |
|_______________|_______________|_______________|_______________________|

SETUP

- follow instructions on page 26 of https://github.com/wb2osz/direwolf/blob/master/doc/User-Guide.pdf
- paste this into build/direwolf.conf "MODEM 120 1200 2200" to replace "MODEM"
- "ADEVICE 2- USB Audio Device" may also be necessary to connect digirig, but most likely it will autoconfigure

RUN

- cd decoder/direwolf_mod/build
- ./src/direwolf.exe

KNOWN ISSUES

- packets drop. May be because we don't do any parity checking before RS decoding. e.g. error detection before error correction
- after some time, it will terminate. unsure why. occasionally throws error but I have had success re-running until it works
- too much noise or double transmission when ptt-press is enabled. currently only working on auto transmission only (ptt edge detection disabled)